        "created_at": "2025-10-18T16:44:34.701Z",
        "cooked": "<p>When you speak an audio-message or also when you listen to one, under certain circumstances, the recording / playback of the audio-message is interrupted.</p>\n<p>This happens e.g. when the screen-rotation changes from portrait to landscape or vice versa while listening / recording. And it also happens when the “low-battery”-system-message appears on screen. (And there was also a third incidence when this happened, but unfortunately I don’t remember it.)</p>\n<p>This is not an iOS-problem and could be done better, because Telegram doesn’t have these problems: in telegram you can play/record audio-messages, while the screen-rotation is changing and when there is a system-message like “low battery” you can discard this, while the audio-message is still playing/recording.</p>\n<p>It would be very nice, if this bug could be fixed.</p>",
